          <p corresp='TTP33745845P0' xml:id='OTP33745845P0'>[seal]
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33745845P1' xml:id='OTP33745845P1'><rs ref='#S63224'>The State of Mississippi<lb/>
Attala County</rs>{
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33745845P2' xml:id='OTP33745845P2'>Personally appeared before me <rs ref='#S32129664'>E L Carnes</rs> an acting <rs ref='#S63172'>Justice of the Peace</rs> for and in the county of Attala County in said State. <rs ref='#S32129103'>Matthew Tubb</rs> &amp; <rs ref='#S32129665'>James H M<add place='above'>c</add>Clintock</rs>, <rs ref='#S32129666'>S. A. Hinds</rs>, <rs ref='#S52938'>A. T. Dubard</rs>, <rs ref='#S32129667'>John H. Tubb</rs> who being duly Sworned deposeth and say that they are and have been near nighbors of <rs ref='#S32049456'>James. B. Ellington</rs> who is now <rs ref='#S69535'>confined</rs> in the <rs ref='#S62926'>county Jail</rs> of Attala <del rend='overstrike'>county</del> &amp; for a number of years <del rend='overstrike'>and</del> have ever since our acquaintance with the said Ellington regarded him as man of <rs ref='#S52163'>unsound mind</rs> and most of the time since the commence=ment of the late war and especially since its termination believe him wholy irresponsible for his acts
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33745845P3' xml:id='OTP33745845P3'>Sworn to and subscribed before me by each one of the party who have hereunto subscribed ther names Given under my hand and seal this the 8<add place='above'>th</add> day of May 1868
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33745845P4' xml:id='OTP33745845P4'>E. L. Carnes <rs ref='#S63172'>J. P.</rs>{
</p>

<p corresp='TTP33745845P5' xml:id='OTP33745845P5'>S. A. Hines<lb/>
Matthew tubb<lb/>
J H McClintock<lb/>
A. T. Dubard<lb/>
John H. Tubb
</p>


        </div>
  </body>
